stylometry: The elasticity of demand is related to the customers purchase decision based on whether or not the price of the product is raised, lowered, or stayed the same.  It is important for companies to analyze the elasticity of demand in order to come up with reasons as to whether or not they should raise the price of their product, lower the price of their product, or keep the price the same.  For instance the elasticity of demand would could be calculated if nike decided to raise the price of their shoes by 5%.  If they jack up the prices of their shoes what is the percentage of peopl that will change their purchase habits and buy another brand.  This is an example of elasticity of demand.
